Please visit http://kcix.net and fill out the small form on the front page or email peering@kcix.net to connect.

Recommended limits to allow for future growth  
IPv4: 200000  
IPv6: 100000

 0:$peerasn to exclude your routes to $peerasn

100GE: $500 MRC, $0 NRC

To celebrate the opening of Denver IX, we are waiving all fees on our 1G and 10G ports, including facility cross-connect fees. Contact us for additional information and to take advantage of this limited-time offer.

You can connect at any of our on-net facilities. Feel free to reach out and we can help coordinate cross-connects!

name: FREMIX
notes:
**FREMIX (Fremont Metro Internet Exchange)**

FREMIX (Fremont Metro Internet Exchange) is a Free Internet Exchange Point (IXP) based in Fremont, California. We are committed to enhancing internet connectivity and performance by facilitating efficient and cost-effective interconnections between local and global networks.

**Locations:**
- Hurricane Electric Fremont 2 ( 48233 Warm Springs Blvd )

**Port Sizes Available:**
- 100mbit / 1G (Via Sponsor Ports)
- 1G Copper / RJ45
- 10G-LR
- 40G-LR4
- 100G-LR4

**Benefits of Peering at FREMIX:**
- Reduced latency
- Improved redundancy
- Lower transit costs
- Enhanced network performance

For more information, visit our website at [www.fremix.exchange](http://www.fremix.exchange)
